s,X_n\n\\in \\mathbb{R}^d$ for large $d$ and $n = poly(d)$ with the promise that a\nsubset of $X_1,\\ldots,X_n$ were sampled from a probability distribution with\nbounded moments, recover some information about that distribution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Nov 2017 18:33:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-21"}
